achievements.title: Theoretical Foundations of Health Research
achievements.description: Gaining a deeper understanding of the research process was a key part of my academic journey. This logbook details the series of lectures I completed on the theoretical foundations of health research. The course was a fantastic opportunity to learn about research ethics, develop skills in synopsis and manuscript writing, and understand the practical steps of bringing a research project to life.

achievements.title: Developing Professionalism and Leadership Skills
achievements.description: My academic journey has always been about more than just knowledge; it's also about building character. This logbook documents my engagement with the "Professionalism" module, which focused on accountability and professional conduct. The sessions honed my skills and understanding of professional behavior in foundational medical subjects and clinical settings.

reflections.title: A case of Intra Arterial Cannulation
reflections.content:
In one of our ECE's, we encountered a short statured patient with deformed limbs and dark skin color.
The nursing staff informed us that IV Cannulation is impossible in these patients because of invisibility of veins owing to darker skins, so they went for Intra Arterial Cannulation.
It was a wonderful interaction between future doctors and Paramedical Staff.
I was amazed to see how important a healthy professional interaction between Medical and Paramedical Staff is for the proper care and well being of the patients.

reflections.title: Dissection of Upper Limb
reflections.content:
It was our first dissection.
From never ever have seen a dead body to making cuts, turning tissues, identitying landmarks and studying structures on a cadaver reeking with the smell of formaline.
And while doing all that, making sure to be extremely careful,gentle, and respectful- to the cadaver who used to be a full of life human being just like us someday - was truly challenging and nerve wrecking.
But, with the passage of time and repeated exposure, we all learn and become experienced.
So did I.
Now, I can perform dissection and study easily without these reprehensions but I try my best to be as respectful and careful with my dead teacher as possible

reflections.title: Summer Research Workshop
reflections.content:
When the part of analysis on SPSS started in the workshop, I just felt so overwhelmed.
I couldn't understand a thing and doubted myself wether I will ever be able to even understand it let alone apply and interpret.
But, fortunately, it was summer vacation.
With the emotional and academic support from my family, I was able to overcome my anxiety.
And at the end of the workshop, not only I applied a couple of tests for statistical analysis but also interpreted them successfully.
